txt.en: 'Upon scouting the encampment of Fushaum Tûm, I have seen many Olog-hai come and go. It seems they have been enslaving Orcs and Easterlings. While I do not care for either's well-being, it can only be a matter of time before the Olog-hai start to capture Gondorians.'

A notice is pinned to the board, signed by Ingold:\n\n'Many Olog-hai have been seen at Fushaum Tûm. A brave adventurer is needed to thwart the Olog-hai gathered there and their plan to enslave Man and Orc alike.'
Defeat Thorakó's Warriors and destroy cages in Fushaum Tum.
Ingold has asked you to defeat Olog-hai and destroy cages in Fushaum Tûm.
You have defeat Thorakó's Warriors and destroy many cages in Fushaum Tum. You continued efforts in Mordor are commended.
Ingold, a soldier of Gondor, has scouted Dor Amarth and is concerned with the growing numbers of foes gathering at the encampment of Fushaum Tûm.
